        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 11 at 2:48PM MDT by NWS Grand Junction CO</headline>
        <description>At 248 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Mount Crested Butte, or 26 miles north of Gunnison, moving northeast
at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Mount Crested Butte and Crested Butte.

This includes Colorado 135 between mile markers 23 and 27.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
